~ parameters: five syntaxes that all bind named values into a node use.
~ pick the one that reads best where you stand. mixing inside one call
~ is an error — the form you open with is the form that closes.


~ ── the five invocation forms (all equivalent) ──────────────────────────────────
~
~   pipes                  @scene |mood calm|
~   parens, space-style    @scene(mood calm)
~   parens, colon-style    @scene(mood: calm)
~   record-arg             @scene { mood - calm }
~   form-fill body         @scene
~                            mood: calm
~                          scene@
~   colon scatter          @scene mood:calm scene@      (single-line body only)
~
~ inside pipes / parens / record-args, value shapes are the same:
~
~   |value|               positional — single word, no !
~   |key value|           named — first word is key, rest is value
~   |key - value|         named — hyphen when the key itself is multi-word
~   |flag!|               boolean — trailing ! marks presence
~   |multi word flag!|    boolean — trailing ! works for any length


~ ── positional ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@figure
|lamp.png|
|caption The second-order Fresnel lens|
figure@


~ ── named ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

~ first word is key, rest is value — no hyphen needed for single-word keys

@scene |mood calm| |location harbour|
The harbour was still.
scene@

~ hyphen escape for multi-word keys

@panel |background colour - dark slate|
The lantern room was unlit.
panel@


~ ── flags ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

~ trailing ! — unambiguous regardless of word count
~ ! mid-value is just punctuation; only the final ! before | counts

@figure
|full width!|
|lamp.png|
|caption The second-order Fresnel lens|
figure@

|dark mode!|
|published!|
|allow line breaks!|

~ mid-value ! is safe — not a flag

|caption Wow! What a lens|


~ ── parens — self-closing, params at the open ───────────────────────────────────
~
~ parens always mean no body. comma-separated. same three forms apply inside.

@badge(tone good, verified!)
@figure(src lamp.png, caption The second-order Fresnel lens, full width!)
@watermark(draft!, label Do not distribute)

~ with body: use open/close and pipes instead

@figure
|src lamp.png|
|caption The second-order Fresnel lens|
|full width!|
Some additional context about this particular lens.
figure@


~ ── pipes scatter, last one wins ────────────────────────────────────────────────

@scene
|mood calm|
The harbour was still.
|mood tense|
Then the bell began to ring.
scene@


~ ── parens, colon-style ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
~
~ inside parens, `:` is interchangeable with space as the key/value separator.
~ pick whichever reads better — colons help when a value also contains spaces.

@figure(src: lamp.png, caption: The second-order Fresnel lens)
@badge(tone: good, verified!)


~ ── record-arg — named params in brace form ─────────────────────────────────────
~
~ a record literal directly after the handle becomes the call's named arguments.
~ self-closing: the matching `}` ends the call. no `name@` close, no body after.
~ field name → capture name. great for citation-style calls in prose.

@figure { src - lamp.png, caption - The second-order Fresnel lens }

~ across lines when the list is long

@figure {
  src - lamp.png
  caption - The second-order Fresnel lens
  alt - A polished Fresnel lens reflecting an evening sky
}

~ colons work as the field separator inside record-args too

@figure { src: lamp.png, caption: The second-order Fresnel lens }


~ ── form-fill body — one param per line ─────────────────────────────────────────
~
~ when the body's first line looks like `key: value`, the whole body is read as
~ named params. the most prose-readable form for many params with long values.

@figure
  src: lamp.png
  caption: The second-order Fresnel lens
  alt: A polished Fresnel lens reflecting an evening sky
figure@

~ values can run across multiple lines if continuation lines indent deeper

@figure
  src: lamp.png
  caption:
    The second-order Fresnel lens, installed at Dunmore Head
    in 1857 and never replaced.
figure@


~ ── colon scatter (single-line body) ────────────────────────────────────────────
~
~ on a one-line body, `key:value` pairs sit beside prose words. values run
~ up to the next whitespace; quote multi-word values with "...". handy for
~ inline calls where a full form-fill body would feel heavy.

The lamp, @figure src:lamp caption:"Second-order Fresnel" figure@, still works.
